"@FeruleBezel @firefox Hi! U2F is disabled by default since it is not a W3C standard. You can enable it in about:config. Mozilla promotes WebAuthn which is a W3C standard that does the same and is enabled by default. The Youbikey demo site uses WebAuthn but Google still uses U2F. #fxhelp"
"@FeruleBezel @firefox how so?"

"@FeruleBezel @firefox W3C does not addopt standards, it makes them. There is usually a draft submitted, several vendors debate, refine and implement it. WebAuthn is based on U2F. It basically makes U2F more flexible. U2F was mostly done by Google and a few fintech companies, not with all the browsers."

"When I had my op last year. 

Could be nothing, could be something... Who knows."
"The same type, being Benign Giant Cell, as these are slow to form then fast growing, if this is one,it more than likely would have been seen"

"Well, looks like I have more appointments again, just when life was getting back to before. 

If it is a Sarcoma again, it's unlikely to be"
"They review previous appointments, test results and ask some questions. From which they then decide to do an urgent MRI, full bloods and..."

"I know something is not right. 

Anyway, GP and I go over the check they want to do. All seems fine, as it did before."
"Fine so far though have had essentially the same symptoms as what I had before the diagnosis, though now and this being a year post op..."
"Today started off well, for a Monday, checked my schedule at work and noted I had an appointment with my GP - follow up re. #Sarcoma tumours"
"Like the weather, in life you have good&not so good;life's a roller coaster.It's how you deal with the experience which make you who you are"
"... "It's simply a moment in time, I see and share with others.""
"Some people ask why I take photos of the sky, my reply "it's not the sky as such that I'm taking a photo of, but the beautiful weather"..."
